3602. Hexadecimal and Hexatrigesimal Conversion


You are given an integer n.

Return the concatenation of the hexadecimal representation of n2 and the hexatrigesimal representation of n3.

A hexadecimal number is defined as a base-16 numeral system that uses the digits 0 – 9 and the uppercase letters A - F to represent values from 0 to 15.

A hexatrigesimal number is defined as a base-36 numeral system that uses the digits 0 – 9 and the uppercase letters A - Z to represent values from 0 to 35.










class Solution {
    string toBase(int n, int base, char* digits) {
        if (n == 0)
            return "0";
        string res;
        while (n) {
            res = digits[n % base] + res;
            n /= base;
        }
        return res;
    }

public:
    string concatHex36(int n) {
        return toBase(n * n, 16, "0123456789ABCDEF") +
               toBase(n * n * n, 36, "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ");
    }
};
